{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"861e5ae7-3a54-4711-8a6a-6a4e32b5611f","content":"In .NET MAUI, you use the **lifecycle events** API in `MauiProgram.cs` via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android =>\n    {\n        android.OnPause(activity => { /* your code */ });\n        android.OnStop(activity => { /* your code */ });\n    });\n#elif IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios =>\n    {\n        ios.DidEnterBackground(app => { /* your code */ });\n    });\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#elif IOS` preprocessor directives to target each platform.\n- `AddAndroid` gives access to `OnPause`, `OnStop`, `OnResume`, `OnCreate`, etc.\n- `AddiOS` gives access to `DidEnterBackground`, `WillEnterForeground`, `OnActivated`, etc.\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` for the extension methods.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8458b16b-b22e-43d1-870a-34b990470211","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's OnPause/OnStop and iOS's DidEnterBackground. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI, not a codebase-specific task.","outputTokens":365,"requestId":"1033:192B19:159270B:182A526:69FD343E"},"id":"7567aedb-f312-4b18-a3fa-c173fb7f3b0d","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:54:30.634Z","parentId":"c6c9a06f-56c6-4729-a068-9a583e963926"}
